title: Estimate the Confidence Interval and Interpret Step by Step
text: Anorexia data PairedData package consist 17 paired data corresponding weights girls treatment anorexia. Test claims patients gain least four pounds weights treatment. Use 0.05 level significance. Assume mean differences approximately normally distributed. can see 95% confidence interval paired mean difference 4.23 Inf. p value 0.03917. plot.meanCI() function visualize confidence interval. Note line true mean(mu) cross confidence interval.  can get document explaining statistical result step step following R code. interpret() function generate document automatically show RStudio viewer. document vignette named “Hypothesis test difference paired means”. Alternatively, can see document default browser.
code: t.test(Anorexia$Post,Anorexia$Prior,paired=TRUE,alternative="greater",mu=4) Paired t-test  data:  Anorexia$Post and Anorexia$Prior t = 1.8807, df = 16, p-value = 0.03917 alternative hypothesis: true difference in means is greater than 4 95 percent confidence interval:  4.233975      Inf sample estimates: mean of the differences                 7.264706 x=meanCI(Anorexia$Post,Anorexia$Prior,paired=TRUE,alternative="greater",mu=4) plot(x,ref="test",side=FALSE) interpret(x) interpret(x,viewer="browser")
